=title> Re: Conquest and Da'kor of Merlin</span><hr size=1> I think the topic of my last post was taken incorrectly.<br>
<br>
I was trying to point out that playing a game that requires an amount of strategy in RvR. If you take a break, or if you don't play all the time, you won't be able to get practiced well enough to take out battle hardened people. Okay, lemme sum it up.<br>
<br>
Warrior 1 fights some times, he doesn't practice swinging his sword, he can't hit as well. He doesn't know all the ways he can be attacked and what every spell every other player has and how to counteract them.<br>
<br>
Now here comes Warrior 2. He fights all the time, he studies the enemy. He spends half his day practicing new ways to slice and dice. He knows how to fight in a battle and has alot of experience.<br>
<br>
Now they meet, and fight. Who the fuck is gonna win?<br>
<br>
For those of you who think warrior 1 because he's just naturaly good at being a warrior. You are fucked in the head. There has never been on Earth a person that could take down a Navy Seal just because he has the mind set of one already and enjoys being a Navy Seal alot.<br>
<br>
No unpracticed person can compare to someone who has trained in every way to kick your ass.<br>
<br>
practice makes perfect the saying goes. This is true even in games, bike riding, running, swimming, ettiqute. And any other fucking thing you can think of. If you do not have any physical or mental handicaps .You can do ANYTHING if you practice enough. <br>
<br>
Time spent in the field, is time practiced. Someone who doesn't do this all the time is going to lose to the one that did.<br>
<br>
Now, let's repeat to get the point across. A large uberguild and it's uberguild ally's will steamroll any not so well organized groups attempt to kill them. PERIOD<br>
<br>
Just because this group of inexperienced fighters may be &quot;naturally better at the game&quot; doesn't mean shit to guys with that much more experience under their belt, god damn.<br>
