<br>
I went for my first RvR experience last night and well got owned. It was good for the experience because I had no real knowledge of what the landscape was and who I was fighting. We didn't have tactical battle plans so of course we were going to get owned. People who play more will always have the advanteg because more experience will give you an advantage. What Tuan is saying that there is also a difference between players in skill and most of that is determined by your ability to take advantage of your advantage or be able to understand the scenario as it layed out for you. <br>
<br>
It looks like RvR would actually be much more fun with 300+ people on each side. Lag of course would be an issue but the battles will be long and require detailed planning and excution. You won't blindly stumble into taking a keep as easy as it may seem now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrechdashadowknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trech Da ShadowKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/9/01 2:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conquest and Da'kor of Merlin</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I was in a pickup raid on naggy last night<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
